This paper is about named entity recognition (NER) using neural architectures, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses methods for domain adaptation, which involves adjusting the model to perform well on data from a new domain, which is a common problem in machine learning. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of standard newswire datasets, which suggests that it could also be relevant to sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
